data.text: Welcome back! In the May/June issue of HorseVibes we’ve mixed it up with a variety of great stories that we’re sure will keep you informed and entertained. Exell by name, excel by nature! Be inspired as Candida Baker digs deep into what gives Boyd Exell, holder of no less than nine consecutive FEI World Cup Driving Championships, that winning edge. Then champion show jumper Vicki Roycroft answers 20 questions, while Tanja Mitton looks at stress and explores to help you create a calmer, more confident take on life. Fine-tune your show ring turnout techniques with a very pretty Training Tips, learn how to feed your pony to happy, healthy, shiny perfection, and join Charlie Brister for some ideas guaranteed to add variety and fun to your training schedule. Plus, plan ahead for your next horse riding holiday with some suggestions from Jane Camens. And then there’s the new addition in our stableyard: The Equestrian Marketplace - your all-things-equine online store, together we are stronger.
